dc:source  a    owl:AnnotationProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_5152  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: \"We used in utero electroporation to introduce expression plasmids into progenitors of excitatory neurons in the cortex (Fig. 5A). We electroporated a myr-tdTomato construct together with an expression plasmid for a GFP-tagged intrabody targeting endogenous PSD-95 (iGFP-PSD-95; Gross et al., 2013), allowing us to visualize dendritic spines and PSDs of excitatory neurons in the mature cortex (Fig. 5A).\n\nWhen combined with Csmd2 immunohistochemistry, we readily found Csmd2 puncta co-localized with PSD-95 at the ends of dendritic spines (Fig. 5B, white arrows). Interestingly, not all PSD-95+ spines displayed detectable Csmd2 signal (Fig. 5B, green arrowheads), indicating some heterogeneity in the presence or levels of Csmd2 at spines.\"\n\nFigure 7, 8: Csmd2 is found in synaptosomal and postsynaptic biochemical fractions and interacts with synaptic scaffold proteins.\n\nBased on the known transmembrane topology of this protein, \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was selected.. Experimental description: Result section, description of localization in Figure 5: \"To begin to test this hypothesis, we used several complementary methods to determine if Csmd2 is localized to synapses in the mouse forebrain.\"" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099061 replaced by GO:0098839" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5152" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

